HILLMAN POWER COMPANY, L.L.C. FERC ELECTRIC RATE SCHEDULE NO. 1
Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service
Hillman Power Company, L.L.C. ("Hillman") provides Reactive Power Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service ("Reactive Supply Service") from a facility located in Hillman Township, Michigan ("Facility") to the Midcontinent Independent System Operator, Inc. ("MISO"). This rate schedule sets forth Hillman's revenue requirement for the provision of Reactive Supply Service from the Facility pursuant to the MISO Open Access Transmission, Energy and Operating Reserve Markets Tariff ("MISO Tariff"). Payments from the MISO shall be in accordance with Schedule 2 of the MISO Tariff under which Hillman receives compensation as accepted by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission.
Hillman's revenue requirement is set forth below.
REVENUE REQUIREMENT:
Fixed Capability Component: Annual Revenue Requirement is $111,659. Fixed Capability Component: Monthly Revenue Requirement is $9,304.92.
